"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-2132016-Transgender-athletes-banned-Olympics\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Transgender women are set to be barred from competing in all female events at theOlympic Games, following a decision by the International Olympic Committee (IOC).\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 19, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trans_woman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Transgender women\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trans_woman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trans_woman\"}, {\"begin\": 126, \"end\": 163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all female events\", \"from\": 57, \"to\": 74}, {\"ngram\": \"theOlympic Games\", \"from\": 78, \"to\": 94}, {\"ngram\": \"a decision\", \"from\": 106, \"to\": 116}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This follows a scientific review that highlighted the enduring physical advantages of those born male.\", \"from\": 165, \"to\": 267, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a scientific review\", \"from\": 178, \"to\": 197}, {\"ngram\": \"the enduring physical advantages\", \"from\": 215, \"to\": 247}, {\"ngram\": \"those born male\", \"from\": 251, \"to\": 266}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Timesreports that the IOC is expected to announce this new policy early next year.\", \"from\": 269, \"to\": 355, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 295, \"end\": 298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2128360110443509e-25, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Timesreports\", \"from\": 269, \"to\": 285}, {\"ngram\": \"this new policy\", \"from\": 323, \"to\": 338}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Until now, the IOC's guidance to Olympic sports has been that transgender women can compete with reduced testosterone levels, leaving it to individual sports to decide.\", \"from\": 356, \"to\": 524, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 371, \"end\": 374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2128360110443509e-25, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic sports\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 403}, {\"ngram\": \"transgender women\", \"from\": 418, \"to\": 435}, {\"ngram\": \"reduced testosterone levels\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 480}, {\"ngram\": \"individual sports\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 513}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, under new president Kirsty Coventry, who has pledged to protect the female category, this stance will change.\", \"from\": 525, \"to\": 643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 554, \"end\": 569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirsty_Coventry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kirsty Coventry\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirsty_Coventry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirsty_Coventry\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the female category\", \"from\": 598, \"to\": 617}, {\"ngram\": \"this stance\", \"from\": 619, \"to\": 630}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The report also states that the committee's medical and scientific director, Dr Jane Thornton, presented the initial findings of the review to IOC members at a meeting in Lausanne, Switzerland last week.\", \"from\": 645, \"to\": 848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 725, \"end\": 738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jane_Thornton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jane Thornton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jane_Thornton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jane_Thornton\"}, {\"begin\": 788, \"end\": 791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2128360110443509e-25, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 816, \"end\": 824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lausanne\", \"score\": 0.9999999999181455, \"rank\": 5.065482726771603e-11, \"text\": \"Lausanne\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lausanne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lausanne\"}, {\"begin\": 826, \"end\": 837, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9997470588936005, \"rank\": 0.00025264707644383905, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The report\", \"from\": 645, \"to\": 655}, {\"ngram\": \"the committee's medical and scientific director\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 720}, {\"ngram\": \"the initial findings\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 770}, {\"ngram\": \"the review\", \"from\": 774, \"to\": 784}, {\"ngram\": \"a meeting\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 812}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thornton, a Canadian former Olympic rower, reportedly told those present that scientific evidence showed there were physical advantages to being born male that remained with athletes, including those who have had trea